Between Whitford's grace (23 March 1498) and the publication of the Adaaia (June 1500) fall Hountjoy¹s stay in Paris, Erasmus' first visit to Tournebem terminating on Feb. 4, and his journey to England, from which he returned to Paris on Feb. ε (Ep. 119). Nothing is known of John Falcon beyond the allusione to him in Epp. so and. 119. It seems from this letter that his home was in Antwerp, and that he knew Batt. He is possibly to be identified with Joannes de Falce Gandavus, to whom Badius dedicated his edition of Solinus, 12 July 1503.]
